<FIRST>r a AM-JumpedShip     06-29 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Jumped Ship,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sailor Literally Jumps Ship</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 19-year-old seaman aboard a Soviet
fishing trawler fired a flare gun and leaped into the Willamette
River on Wednesday in an apparent attempt to defect, police said.
   A fire boat pulled the man from the water and he was taken to a
hospital and treated for a cut lip suffered in the leap, said police
spokesman Henry Groepper.
   Groepper said the man, whose identity wasn't released, told
police in broken English, ``I want to stay here.''
   After he was treated at the hospital, police took the man to the
Portland office of the Immigration and Naturalization Service.
   A woman at the INS office said there would be nobody available to
comment on the incident.
   Groepper said the trawler from which the man jumped, the
Izumrudnyi, is one of two Russian fishing boats on the Willamette
River in Portland.
</TEXT>
