<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Sweden-Slur     06-29 0087</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Sweden-Slur,0089</SECOND>
<HEAD>Immigrant Compensated for Insult</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Supreme Court has ordered a
25-year-old Swede to pay $300 compensation to an immigrant for
calling him a ``darkhead,'' national radio reported.
   The court upheld an appeals court ruling against the man, from
Goteborg in western Sweden, citing laws banning ethnic
dicrimination. Darkhead is seen as disparaging people from the
Mediterranean and elsewhere.
   Those involved were not identified on Wednesday in line with
Swedish press rules, and the ethnic background of the plaintiff not
specified.
</TEXT>
