<FIRST>u a AM-Obit-Wiegert     06-29 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Wiegert,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Original Music Director of ``Cats'' Dead at 59</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMPBELL HALL, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rene Wiegert, the original music
director of ``Cats'' and other hit Broadway shows has died at age 59.
   Wiegert died Monday at Arden Hill Hospital in Goshen. The cause
of death was not given.
   Before his retirement in 1986, Wiegert, a classical musician,
also was the musical director of ``Evita,'' ``Pippin,'' ``The Boys
From Syracuse,'' ``Oh Coward'' and ``Different Times,'' as well as
revivals of ``Oklahoma'' and ``South Pacific.''
   ``Rene Wiegert was an outstanding musician who knew how to get
the best from the singers and players he worked with,'' said
writer-composer Michael Martin Brown, who worked with Wiegert on
``Different Times,'' a Broadway show that opened in 1972 and for
which Wiegert was music director and conductor.
   Wiegert was born March 5, 1930, in St. Louis, and made his debut
at 16 as soloist with the St. Louis Symphony. He graduated in 1951
from the Juilliard School.
   His wife, June Wiegert, an actress and singer, died last year.
Survivors include his fiancee, Brandy Gebhards, and his father.
</TEXT>
