<FIRST>r a AM-People-Backus     06-29 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Backus,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Actor Still in Serious Condition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Jim Backus, who played the
bombastic millionaire Thurston Howell III on the ``Gilligan's
Island'' television show, remained hospitalized Thursday in serious
condition with pneumonia.
   Backus, who also served as the voice for the ``Mr. Magoo''
cartoon character, ``remains under close observation,'' said Saint
John's Hospital and Health Center spokesman Armen Markarian.
   ``There has been no further improvement in his condition,''
Markarian said.
   Backus, 76, has suffered from Parkinson's disease for the past
several years, and was admitted to the hospital more than two weeks
ago for treatment of double pneumonia.
   Backus and his wife, Henny, have produced two humor books based
on his dealing with Parkinson's disease, ``Backus Strikes Back'' and
``Forgive Us Our Digressions.''
</TEXT>
