<HEAD>Communist Politician, Editorial Writer Dead at 86</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mario Melloni, a former Communist Party deputy who
wrote biting editorials for the party newspaper under the pen name
``Fortebraccio'' (``Strongman''), has died at the age of 86.
