<HEAD>Baker Meets with Anti-Apartheid Leader</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Secretary of State James A. Baker III met
Thursday with a leading South African anti-apartheid activist,
Albertina Sisulu, to discuss ways of achieving democratic reform in
her homeland.
   The meeting is one of a number of high level contacts the
administration has had or is planning with South Africans across the
political spectrum.
   Ms. Sisulu, one of three joint presidents of the United
Democratic Front, an anti-apartheid group, will meet with President
