Mrs. Sisulu has served various jail terms and been under house
arrest and other government restrictions for 18 years.
   South Africa gave her a 31-day passport to make the visit, the
first time she's been allowed out of the country.
   Her husband, Walter, is serving a prison sentence since 1964 for
helping found the guerrilla arm of the outlawed African National
Congress.
