<FILEID>AP-NR-06-29-89 0228EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-PurchasingManagers     06-29 0149</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Purchasing Managers,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Group Changes Release Date of Monthly Economic Report</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The National Association of Purchasing Management
says it is changing the release date for its monthly report
surveying corporate purchasing executives on economic conditions.
   The report on the monthly survey, which many experts consider an
indicator of national economic activity, will be issued at 10 a.m.
EDT on the first working day of the following month, beginning with
the June report to be issued Monday, July 3.
   The report previously was distributed to news outlets on the last
Friday of every month, embargoed for release the following Monday.
   However, the group decided to change the method because of
problems with embargo violations, said Linda J. Pope, a spokeswoman
for the Phoenix-based association.
   ``No one will get it in advance,'' she said. ``We want it to be
equitable to all members of the press.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
