<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     06-29 0103</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0107</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yields on 4-Year Notes Fall to Lowest Level in 15 Months</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 4-year Treasury notes fell in
Wednesday's auction to the lowest level in 15 months.
   The average yield was 8.19 percent, down from 9.70 percent at the
last comparable auction on March 29, 1989.
   It was the lowest rate since 4-year notes averaged 7.90 percent
on March 24, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8[
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,978.20.
   A total of $7.53 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$20.34 billion.
</TEXT>
