<FIRST>r f BC-RJR-Changes     06-29 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-RJR-Changes,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>RJR Consoliates Domestic Tobacco Operations</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) _ RJR Nabisco Inc. announced Thursday it
has consolidated its domestic tobacco operations under the name R.J.
Reynolds Tobacco Co. and reorganized the company's senior management
structure.
   The move consolidates R.J. Reynolds Tobacco USA, RJR Sales Co.,
Sports Marketing Enterprises Inc., and R.J. Reynolds Tobacco
Development Co., said James W. Johnston, chairman and chief
executive officer of RJR Nabisco's domestic tobacco subsidiary.
   ``As a single unified company, we will be more competitive, more
responsive to consumers and more cost effective throughout our
operations,'' Johnston said. R.J. Reynolds Tobacco International
Inc. will remain a separate operation, he said, and both companies
will report to Louis V. Gerstner Jr., chairman and chief executive
officer of RJR Nabisco.
</TEXT>
