<FIRST>r f AM-MerrillLynch-Patrick     06-29 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Merrill Lynch-Patrick,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Merrill Lynch Names Thomas Patrick as CFO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomas H. Patrick, a Chicago-based senior
investment banker, was tapped Thursday by Merrill Lynch &amp; Co. to
become chief financial officer for the giant securities firm.
   Patrick, managing director of Merrill Lynch Capital Markets since
1982, will oversee the firm's global controller, treasury, credit,
audit, tax and purchasing operations, in his new post as executive
vice president and chief financial officer.
   He succeeds Courtney F. Jones, who will join the firm's
investment banking division as a specialist in strategic advice to
selected major clients.
   Patrick, 45, a native of Hubbard, Ohio, now living in Barrington
Hills, Ill., was chief financial officer for Life Investors Inc., a
Cedar Rapids, Iowa-based holding company for eight insurance
companies, before joining Merrill Lynch in 1982.
</TEXT>
