<HEAD>Former Frontier President Named To Eastern Board</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Todd Cole, former president of Frontier Airlines,
has been named to the Eastern Airlines board of directors, the
company announced.
   Cole helped reorganize Frontier under Chapter 11 of the federal
bankruptcy code before it was sold to the former People Express
airlines. Texas Air Corp., parent of Eastern, later bought People
Express.
   Cole will be actively involved in the development and
implementation of Eastern's reorganization plan, the company said.
   ``Eastern is fortunate to have a man with the ability and
experience of Todd Cole to assist in the emergence of the company
from Chapter 11,'' Texas Air Chairman Frank Lorenzo said Wednesday.
   Cole also had been vice-chairman and chief financial officer at
Eastern and executive vice president at Delta Air Lines. He was
employed by CIT Financial Corp. from 1969 until 1986, rising to the
chairmanship.
